      "side": 1,
      "message": "This really, really lacks clarity:\n\n\"-my-ip\" is ambiguous because it can lead a candid user to think that the option is used to set the main IP, which is not the case.\n\nIf the IP prefix is always 10.1.2., there is little reason to expose that in the parameter.\n\n\"VM interconnection\" is an ambiguous term, what you really mean is that a virtual lan is being used to connect several emulated systems.\n\nI would suggest using a different name and description, for example:\n\n-shared-net-id \u003cnumber\u003e   \"Activate shared vlan access, using IP address 10.1.2.\u003cnumber\u003e\"",
      "revId": "9700ba6271a939bc9ba81be1b2d5da655d522af8",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889",
